I suppose it should be empty, since its a new String based field in the protobuf schema which should take an empty value when the server parses the message coming from an older client that doesn't populate it:
message StreamInfo {
    string scope = 1;
    string stream = 2;
    string requestedPermission = 3;
}

According to https://developers.google.com/protocol-buffers/docs/proto3,

...
When a message is parsed, if the encoded message does not contain a particular singular element, the corresponding field in the parsed object is set to the default value for that field. These defaults are type-specific:
For strings, the default value is the empty string.
...

Does that make sense?

